{"TopicId":221765,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Planted Flags Not Showing Up In Tracking Station","CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T16:48:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T16:48:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003ESee previous submissions | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 9 3900 12 Core | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0GeForce RTX 2060 Super | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32 GB RAM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs part of the Exploration mode, I went to the Mun Arch and planted a flag right in front of it (first image).\u00A0 When going to the tracking station, even with the Flag filter enabled, the planted flag does not show up (second image).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlanted Flag:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224sEQd0U.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.21\u0022 height=\u0022548\u0022 width=\u0022975\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/4sEQd0U.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTracking Station:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tkaEP6A.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/tkaEP6A.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-22T22:21:15Z\u0022 title=\u002212/22/2023 10:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 22\u0022\u003EDecember 22, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T22:04:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 5 7600X | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Nvidia RTX 4070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32 GB DDR5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this is a missing feature or a bug. What\u0027s the point of planting flags if I cannot see / control / switch to them? I wanted to see locations I\u0027ve visited, but I cannot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T17:58:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Intel Core i7 9750H | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1650 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16 GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFly to the celestial body\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFind monument or/and place flag\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nGo to tracking station\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nTurn on and turn off several times monumet or/and flag filters\u00A0to make sure, that they didn\u0027t appear\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTracking station is not comfortable to be used. I need especially monument filter to work properly so I could easily revisit these locations and collect science with new instruments\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T22:22:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/219348-vl3d/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022219348\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/219348-vl3d/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Vl3d\u003C/a\u003E merged your report\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/223549-vortygont/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022223549\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/223549-vortygont/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Vortygont\u003C/a\u003E merged your report\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phin","CreatedById":229670,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-02T19:00:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 Pro | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A013th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-13600KF 3.50 GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Radeon RX 6800 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32.0 GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a resubmission of the for some reason archived:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed307274194\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/221765-planted-flags-not-showing-up-in-tracking-station/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:194px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTested on 0.2.1.0, flags still don\u0027t persist, and still don\u0027t show up in the tracking station.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mattihase","CreatedById":73161,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-03T17:17:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor me while they don\u0027t show up on the map they seem to persist just fine.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI planted one hovering in the air on one of the launch pads (long story, I made a bug report about it a while back) and it was always there on subsequent launches from that pad. Fortunately, no collision.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-03T17:18:17Z\u0022 title=\u002202/03/2024 05:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Feb 3\u0022\u003EFebruary 3\u003C/time\u003E by mattihase\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Book","CreatedById":213249,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-03-27T06:06:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure if that warrants a separate bug report, but the flags texts are also impossible to read when interacting with it in situ, the only option is to deplant it if an eva kerbal is near.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}